    "visualization_explanation": "The gauge chart configuration represents a univariate dataset measuring engine speed in km/h. The synthetic data point (\u03bc=112, \u03c3=18) simulates real-time telemetry within a 0-200 range. Three pane layers and graduated color bands create depth perception while maintaining data-ink efficiency through Cairo's preattentive processing principles. The semicircular layout follows Tufte's axis design guidelines, optimizing information density through: 1) Inside-positioned ticks reducing chart footprint, 2) Dual-unit minor/major ticks enhancing granularity, and 3) Tri-color danger zoning (safe <120, warning 120-160, danger >160) aligned with industrial safety standards. The central data label uses D3-style '+.0f' formatting for rapid value recognition, while the responsive rules maintain readability across devices."
